Update the test class so it creates at least three different triangles and compares their areas.
Print which triangle has the largest area.

Assisnment 2 - Rectangle object
You are going to create a simple Java program that works with a Rectangle object.
The rectangle should have:
Attributes (fields): length and width
Constructor: to initialize the rectangle with values for length and width
Methods:
getPerimeter() → calculate and return the perimeter of the rectangle
getArea() → calculate and return the area of the rectangle
showInfo() → print the length, width, perimeter, and area

!ADVANCED:
Assignment 3 – Add a Method isEquilateral()

Add a method called isEquilateral() that returns true if all three sides are equal, otherwise false.
Test the method in the test class.

Assignment 4 – Add a Method isIsosceles()

Add a method called isIsosceles() that returns true if at least two sides are equal.
Print the result in showInfo().

Assignment 5 – Add a Method scaleTriangle(double factor)

Add a method that multiplies all sides by a given factor.
Test the method by scaling a triangle and printing the new values.

